        "summary": "## Goal\n- Configure OpenClaw `openclaw.json` with correct thinking model settings (default `medium`, key agents `high`).\n- Ensure only 2 AHV models (`ahvholding/AHV-Holding-DEV`, `ahvholding/AHV-Holding-TroLy`) are used; no other models.\n- Fix `sessions_spawn` sub-agent schema errors (especially `streamTo not supported for subagent`).\n- Configure all 34 Telegram bot accounts with correct usernames, group access, and orchestration settings.\n- Enable automatic group notifications: progress every 5 minutes, daily briefing at 5:00 AM UTC+7.\n- Determine agent-to-group communication architecture.\n- Get MCP Stitch working end-to-end.\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- All changes must be applied to a **backup file** (`/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json.backup-2026-04-12`) for user review before touching the live file.\n- User must explicitly **confirm** before any copy-to-live operation.\n- User wants **each agent to have its own Telegram bot identity** (separate account, not shared identity).\n- User's timezone is **UTC+7 (Asia/Ho_Chi_Minh)**.\n- User wants daily briefing at **5:00 AM UTC+7**.\n- All 34 Telegram bots must be in group `-5212380728`.\n- Real Telegram bot tokens were exposed in chat — must be treated as compromised and rotated.\n- Do not restart the gateway until user explicitly confirms.\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Confirmed correct config key is `thinkingDefault` (not `thinking` or `thinkingLevel`) by inspecting OpenClaw schema.\n- [x] Set `agents.defaults.thinkingDefault = \"medium\"`; set 8 key agents to `thinkingDefault = \"high\"`.\n- [x] Deleted `agents.defaults.models` entry for `anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6` — no non-AHV models remain.\n- [x] Cleaned `agents.defaults.subagents.allowAgents`; configured subagent defaults with `runTimeoutSeconds: 900`, `maxSpawnDepth: 2`, etc.\n- [x] Swapped model priority: default primary → `ahvholding/AHV-Holding-DEV`, fallback → `ahvholding/AHV-Holding-TroLy`.\n- [x] Assigned per-agent models: 19 coding agents → TroLy; 15 orchestration/research agents → DEV.\n- [x] Queried Telegram API for all 34 bots via `getMe` + `getChatMember` to extract real usernames and confirm group membership.\n- [x] Confirmed all 34 bots are `member` in group `-5212380728`.\n- [x] Filled `username` field for all 34 bot accounts in backup (now removed — see below).\n- [x] Added `groups: {\"-5212380728\": {\"enabled\": true, \"requireMention\": false}}` for all 34 bot accounts in backup.\n- [x] Changed daily briefing timezone to `Asia/Ho_Chi_Minh`.\n- [x] Created backup: `/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json.backup-2026-04-12`.\n- [x] Identified root cause of `spawn streamTo` errors: agents pass invalid `streamTo` field for `runtime: \"subagent\"`.\n- [x] **`username` field is NOT valid in TelegramAccountConfig schema**: Removed from all 34 account entries in backup. Schema Telegram account valid fields: `botToken`, `groups`, `enabled`, `allowFrom`, etc. `username` is resolved automatically by Telegram from `botToken` via getMe API.\n- [x] **`crons` key is NOT valid at root level**: Removed from backup.\n- [x] MCP Stitch root cause identified: Service account `agent-sti@agent-stitch.iam.gserviceaccount.com` lacked IAM permission to call Generative Language API. Stitch MCP internally calls `generativelanguage.googleapis.com` which requires `roles/generativelanguage.user` equivalent.\n- [x] **MCP Stitch fixed**: User granted **Generative Language Service Agent** (`roles/generativelanguage.serviceAgent`) role to service account in GCP Console.\n- [x] **Confirmed Stitch MCP works**: Direct API test with OAuth token — `generate_screen_from_text` returns HTTP 200, 24KB response. Prompt `\"Hi\"` → 17s. Detailed prompt → 72s.\n- [x] **API key approach doesn't work**: `X-Goog-Api-Key: AIzaSyAb8...` gives \"API keys are not supported by this API. Expected OAuth2 access token or other authentication credentials that assert a principal.\" The Stitch MCP at `stitch.googleapis.com/mcp` requires OAuth2, not API key.\n- [x] **`stitch-connect` skill has incorrect auth method**: Uses `X-Goog-Api-Key` header which only works for read operations (`tools/list`). `generate_screen_from_text` requires OAuth2. Skill needs correction.\n- [x] MCP Stitch timeout issue: OpenClaw's MCP client has ~60s timeout. Stitch generation takes 17-90s depending on prompt complexity. Short prompts (17s) work fine; long detailed prompts (70-90s) may exceed timeout.\n- [x] Updated `memory/2026-04-12.md` with all findings.\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] Apply corrected backup to live config (after removing `username` from all accounts and `crons` from root).\n- [ ] Test gateway restart with corrected config.\n- [ ] User reviewing MCP Stitch timeout issue — may need prompt length optimization in `stitch-loop` skill.\n\n### Blocked\n- Gateway restart still pending — backup had `username` + `crons` issues (now fixed).\n- `stitch-connect` skill needs correction to use OAuth instead of API key auth.\n- Agent-to-group communication architecture decision still pending.\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **`thinkingDefault` is the correct config key**: Confirmed from schema inspection.\n- **`DEV` is primary, `TroLy` is fallback**: User designated DEV for orchestration/coordinating agents, TroLy for coding agents.\n- **Backup-first workflow**: All changes go into backup; live file unchanged until user confirmation.\n- **`allowAgents` accepts only agent IDs, not tool names**: Corrected.\n- **`sessions_spawn runtime=\"subagent\"` does not support `streamTo`**: Valid fields documented.\n- **`requireMention: false` in backup for group `-5212380728`**: Enables all bots to respond without explicit @mention.\n- **Daily briefing at 5:00 AM UTC+7**: Cron expression `0 5 * * *` with `tz: \"Asia/Ho_Chi_Minh\"`.\n- **`username` field invalid in TelegramAccountConfig schema**: Must be removed from all account entries. Telegram resolves username automatically from `botToken` via getMe API.\n- **`crons` key invalid at root level**: Not supported in installed OpenClaw version (2026.4.9).\n- **MCP Stitch requires OAuth2, not API key**: `X-Goog-Api-Key` header only works for read operations. Screen generation requires `Authorization: Bearer <OAuth2 token>` via service account credentials.\n- **Stitch generation time varies 17-90s**: Short prompts = 17s (fast); detailed prompts with full design tokens = 72-90s (may exceed OpenClaw's ~60s MCP timeout).\n- **`stitch-connect` skill auth method is wrong**: Uses API key which doesn't work for `generate_screen_from_text`. Should use service account OAuth or document that it only supports read operations.\n- **MCP Stitch endpoint**: `https://stitch.googleapis.com/mcp` (OAuth via `Authorization: Bearer <token>` + `X-Goog-User-Project: <project>` headers).\n- **Stitch model options**: `GEMINI_3_FLASH` (default, faster) or `GEMINI_3_PRO` (higher quality). Both require Generative Language Service Agent IAM role.\n\n## Next Steps\n1. **Apply corrected backup to live**: Remove `username` fields (already done), remove `crons` (already done), then:\n   ```bash\n   cp /root/.openclaw/openclaw.json.backup-2026-04-12 /root/.openclaw/openclaw.json && openclaw gateway restart\n   ```\n2. **Test gateway with corrected config**: Verify no schema validation errors.\n3. **Test MCP Stitch via OpenClaw agent**: Send a short prompt to verify full tool chain works.\n4. **Optimize `stitch-loop` skill prompts**: Use shorter, focused prompts to stay within 60s timeout.\n5. **Fix `stitch-connect` skill**: Correct auth method — either document API key limitation for read-only, or update to use OAuth service account approach.\n6. **Decide agent-to-group communication architecture**: Each agent speaks directly in group vs. master-orchestrator as sole spokesperson.\n7. **Fix duplicate Telegram bot tokens**: `senior-architect_bot` ↔ `senior-backend_bot`; `stitch-loop_bot` ↔ `typescript-reviewer_bot`.\n8. **Rotate exposed Telegram bot tokens** via BotFather after gateway restart.\n9. **Test the 2 cron jobs** after restart: progress report at 5-min intervals and daily briefing at 5:00 AM UTC+7.\n\n## Critical Context\n- Live config: `/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json`\n- Backup config: `/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json.backup-2026-04-12`\n- Backup now has `username` removed from all 34 accounts, `crons` removed from root level.\n- Active Telegram group: `-5212380728`\n- User Telegram ID: `6053576134`\n- OpenClaw version: **2026.4.9** (installed at `/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/`)\n- OpenClaw logs: `/tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-04-12.log`, `/tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-04-11.log`\n- Stitch MCP server: spawned by OpenClaw via `npx -y stitch-mcp`; communicates via stdio JSON-RPC.\n- Stitch MCP endpoint: `https://stitch.googleapis.com/mcp`\n- Stitch auth: `Authorization: Bearer <gcloud-auth-token>` + `X-Goog-User-Project: agent-stitch`\n- GCP service account: `agent-sti@agent-stitch.iam.gserviceaccount.com` in project `agent-stitch` (project number `387049750257`)\n- GCP IAM role needed: `roles/generativelanguage.serviceAgent` — **granted by user ✅**\n- MCP client default timeout: ~30s (MCP event wait) + likely ~60s (overall tool call timeout in OpenClaw)\n- Stitch generation time: 17-90s depending on prompt complexity\n- `stitch-connect` skill path: `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/stitch-design/skills/stitch-connect/SKILL.md`\n- `stitch-loop` skill path: `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/stitch-loop/skills/stitch-loop/SKILL.md`\n- All 34 Telegram bots confirmed as `member` in group `-5212380728` with real usernames confirmed via `getMe` API.\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Original Request\nUser (Khương Nịnh) stated that the `stitch-connect` skill only needs the API key they previously sent, and doesn't require OAuth/service account authentication.\n\n## Early Progress\n- Testing multiple Stitch MCP endpoints with API key in different formats (`x-goog-api-key` header, `?key=` query param)\n- `stitch-mcp.googleapis.com` returned 404\n- `stitch.withgoogle.com/mcp` returned 405\n- `stitch.googleapis.com/mcp?key=` with API key in query param returned **200 for `tools/list`** ✅\n- Attempted `generate_screen_from_text` with same API key query param → **401 Unauthorized**\n\n## Context for Suffix\n- The suffix likely contains the error analysis showing Stitch API explicitly rejects API keys for generation with message: *\"API keys are not supported by this API. Expected OAuth2 access token.\"*\n- Conclusion that API key works only for read-only operations (`tools/list`, `list_projects`, `get_project`) but NOT for `generate_screen_from_text`\n- Skill `stitch-connect` description may be misleading about API key scope\n\n<read-files>\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/skills/master-orchestrator/SKILL.md\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/stitch-design/skills/stitch-connect/SKILL.md\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/stitch-loop/skills/stitch-loop/SKILL.md\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/access-B1I79MZ7.js\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/bot-ClNJQIfx.js\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/channel-94kVnXDM.js\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/channel-policy-CrbswhIK.js\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/group-access-hrkZp9Cg.js\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/plugin-sdk/src/config/types.telegram.d.ts\n</read-files>\n\n<modified-files>\n/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/memory/2026-04-12.md\n</modified-files>",
