        "summary": "## Goal\n- Configure 5-minute cron jobs to **only send reports when changes occur**, not on every cycle\n- Keep system documentation accurate (group IDs, agent assignments, cron configs)\n- Recover from gateway restart causing cron timeout errors\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Cron jobs must be silent when no changes detected — no HEARTBEAT_OK messages\n- Only report to Telegram groups when sessions change, agents fail, or blockers appear\n- Master-orchestrator manages both AHV DTLX + QLHV (shared DB) and AHV Works projects\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Updated both 5p cron jobs to **change-detection mode**: compare against `memory/heartbeat-state.json`, stay silent if stable\n- [x] Fixed group ID for DTLX in `MEMORY.md`: `-5168104492` (confirmed via GetIDsBot; DTLX and QLHV share this group)\n- [x] Renamed cron `ed2d0b5d` → **\"5p Progress Report — AHV Works\"**, targets `-5212380728`\n- [x] Renamed cron `6f3323ef` → **\"5p Progress Report — AHV DTLX\"**, targets `-5168104492`\n- [x] Created `memory/heartbeat-state.json` for state comparison tracking\n- [x] Updated `HEARTBEAT.md` to reflect new silent-when-stable logic\n- [x] Increased cron timeout from 120s → **300s** to prevent timeout after gateway restarts\n- [x] Verified 34/34 agent workspaces exist in `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/`\n- [x] Both cron jobs recovered: manual run at 04:34 UTC succeeded, delivered to group `-5168104492`\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] Clarifying DTLX ecosystem group structure: `-5163901258` (session `g-ahv-dtlx-ecosystem`, active with subagents) vs `-5168104492` (cron target, labeled \"QLHV ecosystem\")\n\n### Blocked\n- (none)\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Change detection beats heartbeat**: Cron now uses `memory/heartbeat-state.json` to diff current vs last known state. Only sends to group when something actually changed.\n- **5 consecutive cron timeouts** were caused by gateway restart (~04:22 UTC) making isolated session cold-start exceed 120s. Fixed by increasing timeout to 300s.\n- **Server RAM upgraded**: 3.8GB → 7.8GB after restart.\n- **19 agents still on weaker `AHV-Holding-TroLy` model** (code-reviewer, senior-backend, senior-frontend, etc.) — flagged for potential upgrade but not yet acted on.\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Confirm whether group `-5163901258` (DTLX ecosystem session with active subagents) needs its own cron or is managed differently\n2. Monitor cron jobs to confirm they stay stable after timeout fix\n3. Decide whether to upgrade 19 TroLy-model agents to `AHV-Holding-DEV`\n4. Consider cleaning up stale sessions (old QLHV group, failed subagent sessions)\n\n## Critical Context\n- **Cron job IDs**: DTLX = `6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31` | Works = `ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7`\n- **State file**: `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/memory/heartbeat-state.json`\n- **HEARTBEAT.md path**: `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/HEARTBEAT.md`\n- **MEMORY.md path**: `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/MEMORY.md`\n- **Gateway**: `http://127.0.0.1:18789/` (loopback only)\n- **Failed subagents still in queue**: `code-reviewer`, `prompt-optimizer:subagent`, multiple QLHV backend/frontend subagents\n- **Active DTLX subagents**: `senior-backend:f42cdd0e`, `senior-frontend:cf1f74df` — settings page rebuild + FE refactoring in progress on group `-5163901258`\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Original Request\nKhương Nịnh asks why the master orchestrator for group -5163901258 isn't responding - they haven't seen any feedback.\n\n## Early Progress\n- Assistant checked sessions list and found 22 sessions\n- Discovered a session for group -5168104492 (note: possibly different from the requested -5163901258)\n- Found an April 12 session still running with active subagents handling a settings page rebuild and FE refactoring\n- Mentioned DTLX cron was working again after timeout fix (increased to 300s)\n\n## Context for Suffix\nThe retained suffix shows the master orchestrator providing updates about: the DTLX cron job successfully delivering to group -5168104492 (runs at 04:34 and 04:32 UTC with status: ok), clarification that the cron IS delivering to that group but Lead may be asking about the master not responding to incoming messages, and discussion of multiple active sessions for the group.\n\n<read-files>\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/memory/dtlx-context.md\n</read-files>\n\n<modified-files>\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/HEARTBEAT.md\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/MEMORY.md\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/memory/heartbeat-state.json\n</modified-files>",
