        "tokensBefore": 139407,
        "tokensAfter": 21476,
        "summary": "## Goal\nBuild a **company internal HRM platform** (\"AHV Works\") for AHV Company, with 28 modules covering employee management, time tracking, OKRs, leave management, payroll, internal chat/social recognition, and permissions. The system already exists on GitLab and needs to be reviewed, extended, or deployed.\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Stack must use existing GitLab repos: `ahv-works/ahv-hrm/ahv-hrm-backend` (ID: 78077025) and `ahv-works/ahv-hrm/ahv-hrm-frontend` (ID: 78077037)\n- Backend: Express + TypeScript + MongoDB + Socket.IO + Redis + JWT\n- Frontend: React + TypeScript + Vite + Ant Design + Redux Toolkit\n- No `package-lock.json` (use Yarn)\n- Clean Architecture: Domain, Use Cases, Adapters, Infrastructure\n- All agents must use Node.js, Express, TypeScript, MongoDB, React/Next.js\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Read full Confluence space \"AW\" (AHV Work) — 28 pages of functional specs\n- [x] Connected GitLab MCP, found and enumerated both repos\n- [x] Enumerated all 38 backend modules and 55+ API endpoints\n- [x] Enumerated all 18 frontend modules\n- [x] Cleared previous e-commerce project sessions and files (HANDOVER.md, DESIGN_SYSTEM.md, memory/2026-04-12.md)\n- [x] Explained the code review pipeline in detail\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] User is deciding what to do with AHV Works — pending confirmation on: review (scope?), add features, refactor, or deploy\n\n### Blocked\n- (none)\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Platform = HRM, not CRM**: Despite user calling it \"CRM\", Confluence specs and GitLab repos confirm this is a full HRM (Human Resource Management) system\n- **Source of truth = Confluence AW space**: All functional specs live in `https://dtlx.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/AW`\n- **Auth credentials**: Confluence API token and GitLab token are embedded in `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json` (`mcp` config section)\n- **e-commerce project abandoned**: All sessions killed, all files deleted — not pursued further\n- **Stitch MCP abandoned for now**: Due to permission issues on user project and timeout problems\n\n## Next Steps\n1. User needs to choose: **A) Review code** (with specific scope), **B) Add new features** (Chat, Rankings, Advanced Rewards), **C) Refactor a module**, or **D) Deploy existing system**\n2. If code review: ask for scope (all / specific module / specific file)\n3. If adding features: refer to Confluence specs for what's missing vs. what's built\n4. If deploy: trigger `senior-devops` agent for Docker/CI/CD setup\n\n## Critical Context\n- **Confluence credentials**: `ninhkhuongpl7@gmail.com` / token in `mcpServers.confluence.CONF_TOKEN`\n- **GitLab token**: `glpat-c_N4qQVxbcktRro-S5rdwGM6MQpvOjEKdTpoZDBsYg8.01.170axqn65`\n- **GitLab repos**: `ahv-works/ahv-hrm/ahv-hrm-backend` (78077025), `ahv-works/ahv-hrm/ahv-hrm-frontend` (78077037)\n- **Backend modules**: accounts, employees, departments, positions, attendances, shifts, shiftTypes, leaveRequests, leaveTypes, leaveBalances, checkins, okrs, objectives, keyResults, payrolls, contracts, deductions, incomeTypes, nikoEmotions, nikoGifts, nikoWallets, notifications, systemLogs, globalSettings, roles, permissions, accounts, auth\n- **Frontend modules**: dashboard, employees, departments, positions, attendance, shifts, leave-requests, checkins, okrs, payrolls, contracts, niko-emotions, notifications, settings, account, auth, departments, logs, schedules, positions\n- **Backend swagger**: `https://gitlab.com/api/v4/projects/78077025/repository/files/swagger.yaml/raw`\n- **6 roles defined**: Super Admin, HR, Giám đốc, Trưởng phòng, Leader, Nhân viên\n- **Missing from built system vs. Confluence**: Chat (1-on-1 + group), Social Recognition (peer khen nhau + star points + redeem gifts), Advanced Leaderboard, Full OKR evaluation flow\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Original Request\nUser (Khương Nịnh) asked for a full code review of the AHV Works system with a formal report.\n\n## Early Progress\n- Orchestrator (master-orchestrator) created MEMO.md planning a multi-agent parallel review pipeline\n- Planned 6 review agents: senior-backend, code-reviewer, security-reviewer, database-reviewer, performance-optimizer, senior-frontend\n- Spawned 2 agents so far: **senior-backend** and **code-reviewer** (both running in parallel)\n- Scope: full backend (38 modules, 55+ endpoints) + frontend (18 modules), reading from GitLab BE #78077025 / FE #78077037\n\n## Context for Suffix\nThe conversation was cut mid-spawn. The suffix continues spawning the remaining 4 agents (security-reviewer, database-reviewer, performance-optimizer, senior-frontend) in parallel, then waits for all 6 agents to complete and write findings to individual `.md` files in the reviews/ directory, before the master-orchestrator compiles a final `RELEASE.md`.\n\n<read-files>\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/HANDOVER.md\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/skills/master-orchestrator/SKILL.md\n</read-files>\n\n<modified-files>\n/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/reviews/MEMO.md\n/tmp/conf_fetch.py\n</modified-files>",
